
Overview of noun tolerance

The noun tolerance has 5 senses (first 3 from tagged texts)
                                      
1. (1) tolerance -- (the power or capacity of an organism to tolerate unfavorable environmental conditions)
2. (1) permissiveness, tolerance -- (a disposition to allow freedom of choice and behavior)
3. (1) tolerance -- (the act of tolerating something)
4. tolerance -- (willingness to recognize and respect the beliefs or practices of others)
5. allowance, leeway, margin, tolerance -- (a permissible difference; allowing some freedom to move within limits)
